1
00:00:01,133 --> 00:00:04,367
♪

2
00:00:12,235 --> 00:00:15,098
[Breathing heavily]

3
00:00:26,716 --> 00:00:29,377
[Beeping]

4
00:00:34,844 --> 00:00:36,157
Gator.

5
00:00:36,169 --> 00:00:37,650
Any sign of the sub?

6
00:00:37,660 --> 00:00:39,580
The sonobuoys we placed
in the canal indicate

7
00:00:39,586 --> 00:00:41,392
they're patrolling in a
standard search pattern

8
00:00:41,399 --> 00:00:43,580
here to here.

9
00:00:43,583 --> 00:00:46,114
And with <i>Nathan James</i>
hiding out here in the pass?

10
00:00:46,581 --> 00:00:49,109
They're closing in on us,
sir... Little by little.

11
00:00:49,110 --> 00:00:50,724
How long before they pinpoint our location?

12
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:53,864
It's hard to say, sir, but
it could be a matter of hours.

13
00:00:53,865 --> 00:00:56,193
Once we enter their kill
box, it's a shooting gallery.

14
00:00:56,195 --> 00:00:57,474
If we go deeper into the pass,

15
00:00:57,486 --> 00:00:58,832
it might buy us a little more time.

16
00:00:58,844 --> 00:01:00,325
<i>Chandler: No.</i>

17
00:01:01,328 --> 00:01:03,213
We're not hiding any longer,

18
00:01:03,219 --> 00:01:05,805
and we're not waiting for
Ramsey to make the first move.

19
00:01:05,806 --> 00:01:08,368
If that sub's waiting for
us at the mouth of the river,

20
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:11,727
we go around... Take her on from the flank.

21
00:01:11,728 --> 00:01:13,434
This ends today.

22
00:01:13,442 --> 00:01:15,134
Aye, sir.

23
00:01:21,496 --> 00:01:25,370
♪

24
00:01:37,540 --> 00:01:41,782
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

25
00:01:55,037 --> 00:01:57,429
[Radio chatter]

26
00:02:00,943 --> 00:02:03,571
So, this is where it all happens, huh?

27
00:02:05,525 --> 00:02:07,134
Always with the secrecy.

28
00:02:07,143 --> 00:02:09,200
You wonder why people don't trust you.

29
00:02:09,286 --> 00:02:12,978
I know why people don't trust us... You.

30
00:02:12,979 --> 00:02:15,804
And because of that, four
of my friends are dead.

31
00:02:15,805 --> 00:02:17,118
Well, Sean lied to me, too.

32
00:02:17,130 --> 00:02:19,130
Right. So, which is it?

33
00:02:19,135 --> 00:02:21,660
Are you with us or are you
gonna keep taking shots?

34
00:02:21,661 --> 00:02:23,714
Because we've got work to do.

35
00:02:23,719 --> 00:02:26,143
Can you reconnect to the
Valkyrie Network or not?

36
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:28,534
You have an antenna lead?

37
00:02:39,292 --> 00:02:41,178
Then let's find out.

38
00:02:41,184 --> 00:02:44,046
[Click, device whirring]

39
00:02:44,287 --> 00:02:48,155
So, this woman, Val, is trying
to link back into her network?

40
00:02:48,156 --> 00:02:49,367
As we speak.

41
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:51,400
And you feel we can trust her?

42
00:02:51,405 --> 00:02:53,897
I think she's been won over.

43
00:02:53,897 --> 00:02:56,254
But we'll be observing everything she does.

44
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,608
And we still have no sonar?

45
00:02:58,721 --> 00:02:59,950
No, sir.

46
00:02:59,963 --> 00:03:02,721
Our engineering team is trying
to rig up a depth finder,

47
00:03:02,722 --> 00:03:04,662
but once we go hot with
it, we'll be putting

48
00:03:04,668 --> 00:03:07,459
10 times more current through
it than it was designed for.

49
00:03:07,460 --> 00:03:08,997
So it may burn out?

50
00:03:09,443 --> 00:03:11,430
Could last an hour.

51
00:03:11,435 --> 00:03:13,198
More likely, minutes.

52
00:03:13,206 --> 00:03:14,923
And without it?

53
00:03:15,715 --> 00:03:19,656
No sonar, no way to see that sub.

54
00:03:19,667 --> 00:03:22,900
So you'll just have one shot at them?

55
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:26,532
That's assuming it works at all.

56
00:03:27,253 --> 00:03:28,533
Well...

57
00:03:28,545 --> 00:03:30,431
Should be interesting.

58
00:03:34,307 --> 00:03:37,198
I can't have you here
when it all goes down...

59
00:03:37,199 --> 00:03:39,368
Not you, not Dr. Scott and her team,

60
00:03:39,372 --> 00:03:41,527
not ray and the kids, not the cure.

61
00:03:41,548 --> 00:03:43,231
Especially not the cure.

62
00:03:43,239 --> 00:03:45,832
You can't tell me it's
safer on land than here...

63
00:03:45,902 --> 00:03:47,788
Not with roving immune armies

64
00:03:47,794 --> 00:03:49,623
and non-immunes conned by Ramsey.

65
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:53,928
Mr. President, as of today,
this ship has gone from being

66
00:03:53,929 --> 00:03:55,551
one of the safest places on earth

67
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,479
to one of the most dangerous.

68
00:03:57,485 --> 00:03:58,704
You'll disembark with a team

69
00:03:58,717 --> 00:04:01,964
of our most experienced
operators, led by the X.O.,

70
00:04:01,965 --> 00:04:04,183
along with the other assets
we can't afford to lose.

71
00:04:04,186 --> 00:04:05,667
I understand about the cure,

72
00:04:05,677 --> 00:04:07,767
about Dr. Scott, and about the children,

73
00:04:07,881 --> 00:04:09,294
but I'm the commander in chief...

74
00:04:09,305 --> 00:04:13,309
Which is why you need to
be protected at all costs.

75
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:14,689
You saw what happened

76
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,731
the last time we faced these guys.

77
00:04:16,736 --> 00:04:18,925
There's no real choice here, sir.

78
00:04:25,816 --> 00:04:27,028
<i>Man: Hey!</i>

79
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:29,003
Hey, you see anything over there?

80
00:04:29,008 --> 00:04:30,333
No. You?

81
00:04:30,345 --> 00:04:31,918
Just a matter of time.

82
00:04:31,927 --> 00:04:33,003
Head east.

83
00:04:33,017 --> 00:04:35,542
Navy ship can't hide long in these waters.

84
00:04:39,953 --> 00:04:41,821
<i>Alisha: We've picked up radio chatter</i>

85
00:04:41,822 --> 00:04:43,890
from over a dozen boats in the area.

86
00:04:43,891 --> 00:04:46,113
American civilians are closing in

87
00:04:46,116 --> 00:04:49,572
at the mouths of all the canals
between us and the open sea...

88
00:04:49,763 --> 00:04:52,265
Here, here, here, and here.

89
00:04:52,266 --> 00:04:53,399
We're completely surrounded.

90
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,915
They're forming a blockade...

91
00:04:54,925 --> 00:04:56,978
Trying to force us toward the sub.

92
00:04:58,504 --> 00:04:59,839
How do you know where they are?

93
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,641
I accessed the Deadman Network

94
00:05:01,642 --> 00:05:03,910
and plotted the position of all the phones.

95
00:05:03,911 --> 00:05:06,049
I thought only the immunes
had the deadman game.

96
00:05:06,053 --> 00:05:07,062
They do.

97
00:05:07,077 --> 00:05:08,277
Sir, it looks like

98
00:05:08,290 --> 00:05:10,639
the immunes and the civilians
are working side by side.

99
00:05:10,747 --> 00:05:13,103
Sean Ramsey ordered the blockade directly.

100
00:05:13,153 --> 00:05:14,407
Can't you shut down the network,

101
00:05:14,420 --> 00:05:15,902
keep them from communicating altogether?

102
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:18,270
I built the network so it
can't be killed that way.

103
00:05:18,272 --> 00:05:21,630
You'd have to physically
disable each relay station.

104
00:05:21,631 --> 00:05:22,514
Clever.

105
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:24,918
<i>I</i> thought so.

106
00:05:24,925 --> 00:05:26,406
At the time.

107
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:29,508
Well, we can't just sit
here trapped on the canal.

108
00:05:29,509 --> 00:05:32,572
Give me three operators,
a couple RPGs, and a RHIB.

109
00:05:32,573 --> 00:05:33,956
We'll take out the blockade ourselves.

110
00:05:33,967 --> 00:05:35,717
We're not firing on American civilians...

111
00:05:35,725 --> 00:05:37,644
Under any circumstances.

112
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:41,814
With all due respect, sir, those
civilians fired on <i>us...</i>

113
00:05:41,815 --> 00:05:42,769
Drew first blood.

114
00:05:42,789 --> 00:05:44,990
Lieutenant, the president's right.

115
00:05:44,991 --> 00:05:47,392
Even if we use our non-lethals,

116
00:05:47,393 --> 00:05:49,534
the instant those civilian boats see us,

117
00:05:49,538 --> 00:05:51,692
they'll give our position to the sub.

118
00:05:54,332 --> 00:05:55,866
Then we head right into the ambush...

119
00:05:55,876 --> 00:05:57,871
Take our chances in a dogfight.

120
00:05:57,884 --> 00:05:58,798
No.

121
00:05:58,814 --> 00:06:00,027
There's another way.

122
00:06:00,339 --> 00:06:02,274
I can't kill my network,

123
00:06:02,275 --> 00:06:05,002
but I can flood it with disinformation.

124
00:06:05,911 --> 00:06:09,047
Spoof messages saying
we're somewhere else...

125
00:06:09,048 --> 00:06:11,249
Send the civilians on a wild goose chase.

126
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:12,517
And away from us.

127
00:06:12,518 --> 00:06:14,530
Till someone shows up on a jet ski,

128
00:06:14,535 --> 00:06:16,796
sees there's only open ocean
where we're supposed to be.

129
00:06:16,799 --> 00:06:17,956
Oh, I can take care of that...

130
00:06:17,957 --> 00:06:19,992
Bounce messages off multiple repeaters

131
00:06:19,993 --> 00:06:22,694
so the boats think you're on the move.

132
00:06:22,695 --> 00:06:26,755
Then everywhere they show up,
it'll look like you just left.

133
00:06:26,756 --> 00:06:29,079
And if the sub bought it...

134
00:06:29,502 --> 00:06:31,136
They'd head North, too.

135
00:06:31,137 --> 00:06:34,763
We could send Ramsey racing
to a location of our choosing

136
00:06:34,764 --> 00:06:36,480
and cut him off.

137
00:06:36,488 --> 00:06:38,576
That would be your one shot.

138
00:06:47,285 --> 00:06:50,539
Whew. I can almost smell the jambalaya.

139
00:06:50,540 --> 00:06:52,762
You know, I grew up just
20 miles North of here.

140
00:06:52,765 --> 00:06:54,246
I remember.

141
00:06:54,256 --> 00:06:56,383
What? You figure you're
getting a homecoming dinner?

142
00:06:56,387 --> 00:06:58,063
What do you mean?

143
00:06:58,064 --> 00:06:59,408
You got eyes, don't you?

144
00:06:59,420 --> 00:07:01,665
Even if we beat that sub,

145
00:07:01,668 --> 00:07:04,968
I don't recognize this country anymore.

146
00:07:05,673 --> 00:07:07,762
Well, I guess we'll just
have to work a little harder

147
00:07:07,766 --> 00:07:09,146
to get it back.

148
00:07:09,157 --> 00:07:10,942
Know what I'm saying?

149
00:07:14,047 --> 00:07:16,405
[Indistinct talking]

150
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:25,471
You all right, Radish?

151
00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:27,657
Just lost a bunch of my friends.

152
00:07:27,660 --> 00:07:29,961
Maybe gonna lose the rest of them now.

153
00:07:30,185 --> 00:07:32,943
Ravit was the closest
thing I had left to family.

154
00:07:32,944 --> 00:07:34,358
But we march on, mate.

155
00:07:34,369 --> 00:07:36,355
It's all we can do.

156
00:07:37,703 --> 00:07:39,068
Do you need help with this, sir?

157
00:07:39,079 --> 00:07:40,121
Thank you.

158
00:07:40,136 --> 00:07:41,449
What's your name, son?

159
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,369
Ray Diaz.

160
00:07:42,385 --> 00:07:44,069
Future secret service man.

161
00:07:44,077 --> 00:07:45,747
[Chuckles]

162
00:07:45,755 --> 00:07:47,222
Hey, Doc.

163
00:07:47,499 --> 00:07:48,879
[Gun cocks]

164
00:07:49,249 --> 00:07:51,034
Just in case.

165
00:07:53,922 --> 00:07:56,920
Clips to your belt. Wraps
around your upper thigh.

166
00:07:57,493 --> 00:07:59,345
I'll let <i>you</i> put it on.

167
00:08:13,972 --> 00:08:15,488
Lieutenant.

168
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,233
Lieutenant.

169
00:08:19,245 --> 00:08:21,046
You doing okay?

170
00:08:21,047 --> 00:08:23,977
Good as I <i>can</i> be.

171
00:08:27,786 --> 00:08:30,367
Stay safe out there, okay?

172
00:08:30,368 --> 00:08:32,465
You too.

173
00:08:37,321 --> 00:08:38,735
Kara.

174
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:44,606
This sub...

175
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:47,200
You've beaten them before.

176
00:08:47,340 --> 00:08:49,764
You'll sink it this time.

177
00:08:56,693 --> 00:09:00,954
Don't you dare make me
raise this child by myself.

178
00:09:00,955 --> 00:09:03,118
That will not happen.

179
00:09:03,122 --> 00:09:05,243
Okay?

180
00:09:10,871 --> 00:09:12,252
[Chuckles]

181
00:09:12,263 --> 00:09:14,418
[Chuckles]

182
00:09:20,482 --> 00:09:23,102
I'll see you soon.

183
00:09:23,773 --> 00:09:25,423
Okay.

184
00:09:35,497 --> 00:09:37,552
Figures the one time you
don't go with the land team,

185
00:09:37,557 --> 00:09:39,524
all the action's gonna be on the ship.

186
00:09:39,525 --> 00:09:41,159
The cure's the thing.

187
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,258
Whatever happens,

188
00:09:42,272 --> 00:09:44,394
I know you'll get it where it needs to go.

189
00:09:44,509 --> 00:09:46,293
It's coming right back here.

190
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:48,151
I'm glad you're so confident.

191
00:09:48,167 --> 00:09:49,568
Well, it sucks, though.

192
00:09:49,569 --> 00:09:51,336
I really wanted to be there

193
00:09:51,337 --> 00:09:53,660
when you sank that son of a bitch.

194
00:10:00,145 --> 00:10:02,758
For my family.

195
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,002
Understood.

196
00:10:08,246 --> 00:10:09,847
[Inhales deeply]

197
00:10:10,119 --> 00:10:11,938
Commander.

198
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:13,459
Commander.

199
00:10:14,921 --> 00:10:17,010
Land teams, let's load up the RHIBs.

200
00:10:17,014 --> 00:10:19,168
Move out!

201
00:10:19,172 --> 00:10:21,462
♪

202
00:10:59,066 --> 00:11:01,402
<i>Slattery: Burk, Miller, you're on POTUS.</i>

203
00:11:01,403 --> 00:11:03,773
Walkies are off. All
comms are face-to-face.

204
00:11:03,775 --> 00:11:05,903
We do not, under any circumstances,

205
00:11:05,907 --> 00:11:07,330
make contact with the ship.

206
00:11:07,535 --> 00:11:09,184
We are officially dark

207
00:11:09,193 --> 00:11:13,054
till we hear from them that
they've killed that sub.

208
00:11:21,021 --> 00:11:24,692
We'll be putting juice
down all 50 leads now.

209
00:11:24,693 --> 00:11:26,836
It's gonna light up like a flashbulb.

210
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:28,793
[Grunts]

211
00:11:29,069 --> 00:11:30,431
How's it coming?

212
00:11:30,432 --> 00:11:31,965
About halfway through, ma'am.

213
00:11:31,966 --> 00:11:33,701
Thanks for your help, Master Chief.

214
00:11:33,702 --> 00:11:35,969
Kind of shorthanded down here.

215
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:37,337
Brilliant idea, ma'am...

216
00:11:37,338 --> 00:11:40,063
Turning the depth finder
into a sub-hunting sonar.

217
00:11:40,064 --> 00:11:42,853
Yeah, well, it's only
brilliant if it works.

218
00:11:43,511 --> 00:11:45,579
<i>Chandler: We're betting
that the sub is roughly here.</i>

219
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,926
We're gonna spoof that we're
at the mouth of Quarantine Bay.

220
00:11:47,928 --> 00:11:50,375
That should draw the civilians
out of the waterways north.

221
00:11:50,376 --> 00:11:53,001
If the sub takes the bait,
they'll head along this route.

222
00:11:53,002 --> 00:11:54,617
That's where they'll get the most depth.

223
00:11:54,626 --> 00:11:56,740
- And stealth.
- Yes, sir.

224
00:11:56,744 --> 00:11:59,535
Assuming the civilians clear
the blockade and head upriver,

225
00:11:59,536 --> 00:12:01,457
we'll make the turn out of pass a loutre

226
00:12:01,463 --> 00:12:03,397
and head northeast up
through the Main Pass.

227
00:12:03,398 --> 00:12:06,167
And if all goes as planned,
we'll make contact right here.

228
00:12:06,168 --> 00:12:08,826
Hit them while they're
looking the other way.

229
00:12:08,827 --> 00:12:10,631
We'll need to be completely silent

230
00:12:10,638 --> 00:12:13,073
when we reach the opening, or
the sub will hear us coming.

231
00:12:13,074 --> 00:12:14,475
So we build up a good head of steam,

232
00:12:14,476 --> 00:12:16,243
kill the engines, and
coast into open water,

233
00:12:16,244 --> 00:12:18,545
light up that sonar, and
fire at whatever's there.

234
00:12:18,546 --> 00:12:20,547
Once sonar's up, we can fix target and fire

235
00:12:20,548 --> 00:12:21,715
in less than 10 seconds, sir.

236
00:12:21,716 --> 00:12:22,961
Very well.

237
00:12:23,753 --> 00:12:25,168
Sir, we have a remote connect with CESS

238
00:12:25,179 --> 00:12:26,693
so Val can work from here.

239
00:12:26,721 --> 00:12:27,904
This goes wrong, a lot of people

240
00:12:27,917 --> 00:12:29,735
are gonna get caught in the crossfire.

241
00:12:29,742 --> 00:12:30,986
It'll work.

242
00:12:33,227 --> 00:12:34,995
Time to flood the network, then.

243
00:12:34,996 --> 00:12:36,497
Let Ramsey's armada know

244
00:12:36,498 --> 00:12:39,723
<i>Nathan James</i> has
been spotted and on the move.

245
00:12:39,724 --> 00:12:41,744
Start now.

246
00:12:43,103 --> 00:12:45,832
[Exhales shakily, clears throat]

247
00:12:48,089 --> 00:12:49,436
[Sighs]

248
00:12:49,448 --> 00:12:52,377
[Keyboard clacking]

249
00:12:54,016 --> 00:12:55,498
Relax.

250
00:12:55,508 --> 00:12:57,326
I'm not a double agent.

251
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:58,651
I'm on the ship, too.

252
00:12:58,663 --> 00:13:00,784
I'm not worried.

253
00:13:00,788 --> 00:13:03,412
First sign you're not on our side,

254
00:13:03,413 --> 00:13:04,762
I'll kill you myself.

255
00:13:04,774 --> 00:13:06,517
[Chuckles]

256
00:13:15,992 --> 00:13:18,493
[Beeping]

257
00:13:18,937 --> 00:13:22,882
Sir, incoming messages indicate
civilians are responding.

258
00:13:22,883 --> 00:13:25,608
They're on the move. Looks
like they're buying it.

259
00:13:25,609 --> 00:13:27,394
On the move and headed North.

260
00:13:27,401 --> 00:13:29,958
Just make sure you don't
put us too far east.

261
00:13:29,959 --> 00:13:32,841
We need that sub to cross the
mouth of the northern pass.

262
00:13:32,842 --> 00:13:35,704
O.O.D., get the ship under way.

263
00:13:36,195 --> 00:13:37,844
Let's move.

264
00:13:37,853 --> 00:13:39,813
Aye, sir.

265
00:13:45,188 --> 00:13:47,435
Hell of a day to sink a ship, is it not?

266
00:13:47,439 --> 00:13:49,325
Right. Yeah!

267
00:13:49,331 --> 00:13:50,610
Any news?

268
00:13:50,622 --> 00:13:51,934
Not yet.

269
00:13:52,073 --> 00:13:53,507
The plan's closing in on him, though.

270
00:13:53,508 --> 00:13:56,647
Civilians got all the
escape routes blockaded now.

271
00:13:56,648 --> 00:13:58,712
They'll flush them right out
to us, and then it's over.

272
00:13:58,713 --> 00:14:00,781
- [Beep]
- Multiple sightings of the destroyer, sir.

273
00:14:00,782 --> 00:14:02,363
Speak of the devil. Where?

274
00:14:02,372 --> 00:14:05,549
Says here Quarantine Bay.

275
00:14:11,098 --> 00:14:13,826
You slippery bastard.

276
00:14:16,089 --> 00:14:18,765
Must have flown the Coop
before the blockade formed.

277
00:14:18,766 --> 00:14:20,695
Well, so much for your American armada.

278
00:14:20,701 --> 00:14:23,169
They let a 500-foot
ship get right past them.

279
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:24,328
Fret not, Bruv.

280
00:14:24,342 --> 00:14:26,612
I've got a contingency on
land for this very reason.

281
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:28,467
Have Ian ready the rocket battery.

282
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:30,027
We're gonna give him something to shoot at.

283
00:14:30,037 --> 00:14:31,584
Right, Guv.

284
00:14:31,811 --> 00:14:33,258
We got them.

285
00:14:34,813 --> 00:14:37,676
Don't lose faith in me now.

286
00:14:41,327 --> 00:14:45,453
Set a new course - come 295,
Quarantine Bay.

287
00:14:45,454 --> 00:14:46,921
All ahead full.

288
00:14:46,931 --> 00:14:50,333
Aye, sir. Setting new course, 295.

289
00:14:52,783 --> 00:14:55,451
♪

290
00:15:02,233 --> 00:15:04,254
Around the next bend is where we estimated

291
00:15:04,259 --> 00:15:06,548
the American blockade to be, sir.

292
00:15:06,652 --> 00:15:08,807
You sure they're all gone.

293
00:15:08,811 --> 00:15:10,409
Should be.

294
00:15:10,418 --> 00:15:13,381
Everyone with a phone, at least.

295
00:15:22,141 --> 00:15:23,589
C.I.C., bridge.

296
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,743
Bring all non-lethal
countermeasures online.

297
00:15:25,747 --> 00:15:28,037
If there are American
boats around this bend,

298
00:15:28,039 --> 00:15:29,453
we do not shoot to kill.

299
00:15:29,464 --> 00:15:30,271
T.A.O., aye.

300
00:15:30,288 --> 00:15:32,442
Combat, ready LAWS and LRAD.

301
00:15:35,884 --> 00:15:37,703
<i>Gator: Here we go, sir.</i>

302
00:15:44,077 --> 00:15:46,199
♪

303
00:16:06,512 --> 00:16:08,197
<i>Chandler: First time in my life,</i>

304
00:16:08,205 --> 00:16:11,280
I'm hoping not to see any Americans.

305
00:16:31,828 --> 00:16:33,950
[Exhales deeply]

306
00:16:33,954 --> 00:16:36,478
It worked.

307
00:16:36,479 --> 00:16:38,128
Good job.

308
00:16:38,718 --> 00:16:40,133
Now keep it going.

309
00:16:46,609 --> 00:16:50,592
[Keyboard clacking]

310
00:16:52,234 --> 00:16:54,255
♪

311
00:16:54,260 --> 00:16:57,999
[Animals chattering]

312
00:16:58,449 --> 00:16:59,997
This is it.

313
00:17:00,007 --> 00:17:02,864
Taylor, Miller, Cruz, set security.

314
00:17:07,703 --> 00:17:10,128
Ray, I think it's time
you got your people fed.

315
00:17:10,129 --> 00:17:12,651
Remember, rations might
have to last us the week.

316
00:17:12,651 --> 00:17:14,132
All right, guys, chow time.

317
00:17:14,142 --> 00:17:16,172
Two granola bars each
and half a liter of water.

318
00:17:16,177 --> 00:17:19,175
Next meal's at 1900.

319
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:24,918
Next mark... Southeast corner of Black Bay.

320
00:17:24,998 --> 00:17:26,209
Got it.

321
00:17:26,222 --> 00:17:27,695
[Beep]

322
00:17:27,705 --> 00:17:30,396
We're keeping the American
armada on the move, sir.

323
00:17:30,397 --> 00:17:33,222
If the sub has joined the
hunt, I estimate they're here,

324
00:17:33,223 --> 00:17:34,771
heading right for our ambush.

325
00:17:34,781 --> 00:17:36,385
How long till we're out of the canal?

326
00:17:36,394 --> 00:17:37,458
10 minutes, sir.

327
00:17:37,472 --> 00:17:38,880
Perfect.

328
00:17:42,213 --> 00:17:43,594
CCS, bridge.

329
00:17:43,605 --> 00:17:45,389
Stand by to go hot with the sonar.

330
00:17:45,396 --> 00:17:46,510
I want to test her out.

331
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:47,831
Copy that, sir.

332
00:17:51,615 --> 00:17:53,209
Go ahead, Eng.

333
00:17:53,789 --> 00:17:56,841
Sending juice to the sonar head.

334
00:17:57,709 --> 00:18:00,740
[Machinery whirring]

335
00:18:04,887 --> 00:18:06,739
- [Sizzle]
- [Gasps]

336
00:18:06,746 --> 00:18:09,382
Ma'am, you can cook a steak on this thing.

337
00:18:09,659 --> 00:18:11,912
It's gonna get even
hotter once we go active.

338
00:18:11,915 --> 00:18:13,399
Ma'am, can you call the Galley

339
00:18:13,409 --> 00:18:15,321
and have them start sending buckets of ice?

340
00:18:15,327 --> 00:18:18,635
I'll organize a team.

341
00:18:19,353 --> 00:18:20,902
Whew.

342
00:18:40,621 --> 00:18:43,660
Hardest thing about goodbye is...

343
00:18:44,481 --> 00:18:47,862
All the things you didn't say.

344
00:18:48,527 --> 00:18:53,007
All the... Unresolved stuff...

345
00:18:53,434 --> 00:18:57,140
Your feelings, whatnot.

346
00:18:59,188 --> 00:19:01,546
You and the captain...

347
00:19:03,352 --> 00:19:06,485
You'll get a chance to
say what you need to.

348
00:19:10,509 --> 00:19:12,361
The hell is that?

349
00:19:20,509 --> 00:19:22,561
<i>Rachel: That child is sick.</i>

350
00:19:22,566 --> 00:19:24,126
Shh. Stay put.

351
00:19:24,136 --> 00:19:25,137
You want me to stay put

352
00:19:25,152 --> 00:19:26,847
when you know very well
that I can heal her?

353
00:19:26,856 --> 00:19:29,284
Until this battle is over,
we don't exist out here.

354
00:19:29,285 --> 00:19:31,170
Once the captain gives the all-clear,

355
00:19:31,176 --> 00:19:32,597
we can go after them if you want.

356
00:19:32,608 --> 00:19:35,139
By which stage, she'll be dead.

357
00:19:37,495 --> 00:19:38,607
Excuse me.

358
00:19:38,621 --> 00:19:40,091
- Damn it!
- Wait! Dr. Scott!

359
00:19:40,101 --> 00:19:42,994
[Panting]

360
00:19:43,143 --> 00:19:45,769
E-excuse me. The girl is sick.

361
00:19:45,776 --> 00:19:46,690
[Guns cock]

362
00:19:46,706 --> 00:19:47,715
Hold it!

363
00:19:47,730 --> 00:19:49,518
Whoa! Whoa!

364
00:19:50,674 --> 00:19:51,617
Listen to me.

365
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:53,349
Not another step, or I'll shoot!

366
00:19:53,357 --> 00:19:55,310
The girl is sick.

367
00:19:55,316 --> 00:19:56,713
You <i>all</i> are.

368
00:19:56,829 --> 00:19:58,494
- We have the cure.
- Got him.

369
00:19:58,495 --> 00:19:59,638
Hold your fire, Burk.

370
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:02,079
I can help you.

371
00:20:02,092 --> 00:20:03,673
Don't lie to me! I know what you are!

372
00:20:03,682 --> 00:20:05,069
I'm not lying to you.

373
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:07,069
- I got the shot. I can take him.
- Hold your fire.

374
00:20:07,070 --> 00:20:09,772
Y'all stay back! We don't want no trouble!

375
00:20:09,773 --> 00:20:11,140
[Velcro rips]

376
00:20:11,141 --> 00:20:13,703
Easy, cowboy.

377
00:20:14,352 --> 00:20:16,946
I'm gonna treat the child.

378
00:20:19,081 --> 00:20:21,372
If you want to stop me,

379
00:20:21,561 --> 00:20:24,491
you're gonna have to shoot me.

380
00:20:25,411 --> 00:20:27,082
All right?

381
00:20:27,090 --> 00:20:29,143
Stay back.

382
00:20:30,974 --> 00:20:32,457
Mase.

383
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:35,025
Stay back!

384
00:20:38,051 --> 00:20:40,038
Lower it, Mase!

385
00:20:40,738 --> 00:20:42,928
It's all right.

386
00:20:55,146 --> 00:20:57,269
It's all right.

387
00:21:18,246 --> 00:21:20,347
Give me your hands.

388
00:21:49,505 --> 00:21:52,435
You said you could cure my daughter.

389
00:21:57,943 --> 00:22:00,841
I already have.

390
00:22:08,289 --> 00:22:11,355
I already have.

391
00:22:16,775 --> 00:22:20,343
<i>Mase: Sorry we came at you like
that. We thought you was immunes.</i>

392
00:22:20,344 --> 00:22:22,111
We was sure of it, the way you came at us.

393
00:22:22,112 --> 00:22:23,780
No one was wearing any masks.

394
00:22:23,781 --> 00:22:26,049
They was the ones gave us the sickness...

395
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:27,517
At one of they camps.

396
00:22:27,518 --> 00:22:31,254
Wrapped my daughter up in
one of they infected blankets.

397
00:22:31,255 --> 00:22:32,956
Couple days later...

398
00:22:32,957 --> 00:22:35,692
First sign of the fever,
they kicked us out.

399
00:22:35,693 --> 00:22:36,917
We found a car,

400
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:39,389
but it died on the road
a few miles North of here.

401
00:22:39,539 --> 00:22:40,921
Where were you headed?

402
00:22:41,065 --> 00:22:42,496
Back home.

403
00:22:42,507 --> 00:22:44,662
To do what?

404
00:22:47,326 --> 00:22:49,279
To be together.

405
00:22:53,009 --> 00:22:55,266
You're not gonna die.

406
00:22:56,512 --> 00:22:59,677
The cure is contagious as the common cold.

407
00:23:02,235 --> 00:23:04,054
You sure you don't want
to give them the shot?

408
00:23:04,061 --> 00:23:05,955
You never tried this on a human before.

409
00:23:05,956 --> 00:23:08,202
It's gonna work, Tex.

410
00:23:08,669 --> 00:23:10,116
All right.

411
00:23:10,127 --> 00:23:11,628
<i>Slattery: Lieutenant Green,</i>

412
00:23:11,629 --> 00:23:13,763
bring these people some
M.R.E.S and water, please.

413
00:23:13,764 --> 00:23:15,245
Yes, sir.

414
00:23:16,574 --> 00:23:18,167
Y'all with the Navy, then.

415
00:23:18,168 --> 00:23:20,222
Yes, ma'am.

416
00:23:21,011 --> 00:23:22,693
We should tell them.

417
00:23:23,273 --> 00:23:24,574
Tell us what?

418
00:23:24,575 --> 00:23:27,009
When we were there at the immune camp,

419
00:23:27,010 --> 00:23:29,045
yesterday morning, right before we left,

420
00:23:29,046 --> 00:23:30,880
we heard some people talking.

421
00:23:30,881 --> 00:23:33,482
They said some English ones from the sub

422
00:23:33,483 --> 00:23:35,839
was bringing something to Lomas Point...

423
00:23:35,953 --> 00:23:37,620
Something to sink your ship.

424
00:23:37,621 --> 00:23:39,322
What do you mean, "something"?

425
00:23:39,323 --> 00:23:42,719
I got the idea it was
some kind of gun or tank...

426
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:43,762
Serious artillery.

427
00:23:44,049 --> 00:23:45,698
They just said it was something big

428
00:23:45,707 --> 00:23:47,525
and it could take you out.

429
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:53,135
If it's a threat, we better warn them.

430
00:23:53,136 --> 00:23:55,304
Yeah, if we warn them, it could
give up <i>both</i> our positions.

431
00:23:55,305 --> 00:23:57,139
Well, then, we got to
go after them ourselves.

432
00:23:57,140 --> 00:23:59,542
Lomas Point's just a
few miles north of here.

433
00:23:59,543 --> 00:24:00,874
Mr. president?

434
00:24:00,886 --> 00:24:02,704
Do what you got to do.

435
00:24:03,646 --> 00:24:05,801
We'll be fine here.

436
00:24:06,664 --> 00:24:08,045
Tex, Green, gear up.

437
00:24:08,056 --> 00:24:10,326
We take one RHIB. Everyone else stays put.

438
00:24:14,795 --> 00:24:17,557
Burk, it's on <i>you</i> now here.

439
00:24:17,817 --> 00:24:21,326
Don't worry, X.O. I got it.

440
00:24:30,946 --> 00:24:32,327
[Beeping]

441
00:24:32,338 --> 00:24:34,729
Lots of sightings, sir.

442
00:24:41,855 --> 00:24:44,837
Ship's on the move again...
Heading north-northwest.

443
00:24:44,838 --> 00:24:46,588
It's all the way up to Black Bay.

444
00:24:46,596 --> 00:24:48,886
<i>Sean: He's moving fast.</i>

445
00:24:48,888 --> 00:24:51,818
Too fast for someone trying
to tiptoe around a sub.

446
00:24:55,314 --> 00:24:57,201
Bloody hell.

447
00:24:57,207 --> 00:24:58,856
Val.

448
00:25:02,039 --> 00:25:04,835
Stand by to go hot with the sonar.

449
00:25:07,243 --> 00:25:09,230
♪

450
00:25:10,421 --> 00:25:13,849
All engines stop. E-stop all main engines.

451
00:25:13,850 --> 00:25:15,951
CCS, bridge, e-stop all main engines.

452
00:25:15,952 --> 00:25:17,987
- All stop, aye.
- Feather props.

453
00:25:17,988 --> 00:25:19,722
We're drifting into the fight zone.

454
00:25:19,723 --> 00:25:21,490
Keep an eye on our speed as we decelerate.

455
00:25:21,491 --> 00:25:23,360
If we start to lose
steerage, I want to know.

456
00:25:23,366 --> 00:25:24,914
Aye, sir.

457
00:25:36,317 --> 00:25:37,563
CCS, captain.

458
00:25:37,576 --> 00:25:39,162
On my call, fire it up.

459
00:25:39,171 --> 00:25:40,483
Aye, sir.

460
00:25:42,552 --> 00:25:46,291
C.I.C., prepare to calculate
a fire-control solution.

461
00:25:46,451 --> 00:25:48,653
T.A.O., aye.

462
00:25:53,095 --> 00:25:54,105
Now.

463
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,129
[Grunts]

464
00:25:55,144 --> 00:25:57,611
[Machinery whirring]

465
00:26:00,629 --> 00:26:02,213
[Sonar pinging]

466
00:26:03,152 --> 00:26:04,331
Where are they?

467
00:26:04,344 --> 00:26:06,094
[Chirp]

468
00:26:06,102 --> 00:26:07,704
Shut it down.

469
00:26:09,222 --> 00:26:10,669
[Whirring stops]

470
00:26:13,108 --> 00:26:14,118
What the hell?

471
00:26:14,133 --> 00:26:15,377
What?

472
00:26:15,390 --> 00:26:17,074
I could swear I just heard something.

473
00:26:17,082 --> 00:26:18,268
We got pinged?

474
00:26:18,281 --> 00:26:20,840
No, it was an echo off the sea bottom.

475
00:26:21,195 --> 00:26:23,183
But it's gone now.

476
00:26:23,188 --> 00:26:25,048
Go active sonar?

477
00:26:25,055 --> 00:26:26,704
No. Not yet.

478
00:26:39,995 --> 00:26:41,679
How much speed left?

479
00:26:41,687 --> 00:26:42,893
6 knots, sir.

480
00:26:42,906 --> 00:26:44,506
We lose steering at 3 1/2,

481
00:26:44,507 --> 00:26:46,609
approximately 90 seconds from now.

482
00:26:46,962 --> 00:26:49,420
I can't spoof you any deeper into the bay.

483
00:26:49,421 --> 00:26:52,249
It'll look like you're on land.

484
00:26:56,652 --> 00:26:57,986
T.A.O.

485
00:26:57,987 --> 00:27:00,462
Roll F.I.S. Green. Ready torpedoes.

486
00:27:00,462 --> 00:27:01,471
T.A.O., aye.

487
00:27:01,486 --> 00:27:02,495
[Beep]

488
00:27:02,510 --> 00:27:03,579
F.I.S. is green.

489
00:27:03,593 --> 00:27:04,840
On my mark.

490
00:27:04,853 --> 00:27:05,728
Target, sir?

491
00:27:05,729 --> 00:27:07,243
I'm working on it.

492
00:27:16,688 --> 00:27:18,271
Speed?

493
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:20,098
4 1/2.

494
00:27:29,270 --> 00:27:31,597
<i>- Ned: What are you doing?</i>
- Shh.

495
00:27:31,772 --> 00:27:34,028
He's close.

496
00:27:40,545 --> 00:27:43,104
Helmsman...

497
00:27:43,105 --> 00:27:45,226
Come right.

498
00:27:45,230 --> 00:27:47,659
Steer course 0-9-5.

499
00:27:47,910 --> 00:27:49,492
Aye, sir.

500
00:28:07,915 --> 00:28:09,330
Sonar.

501
00:28:09,341 --> 00:28:10,671
You got one more in you?

502
00:28:10,683 --> 00:28:12,703
Ready as we'll ever be, sir.

503
00:28:12,708 --> 00:28:14,863
Fire it up on my call.

504
00:28:20,769 --> 00:28:23,093
Spin the prop a moment.

505
00:28:23,095 --> 00:28:26,654
Full slow, rudder a touch to port.

506
00:28:26,655 --> 00:28:28,338
Aye, sir.

507
00:28:31,702 --> 00:28:33,285
Light it up.

508
00:28:33,294 --> 00:28:34,235
[Grunts]

509
00:28:34,251 --> 00:28:36,339
[Machinery whirring]

510
00:28:36,343 --> 00:28:38,127
Keep 'em coming!

511
00:28:38,924 --> 00:28:41,990
[Sonar pinging]

512
00:28:43,892 --> 00:28:46,083
Contact! They're here!

513
00:28:46,086 --> 00:28:48,174
[Pinging continues]

514
00:28:48,392 --> 00:28:49,873
Son of a...

515
00:28:49,883 --> 00:28:51,835
Where?

516
00:28:58,168 --> 00:29:01,244
He's right below us.

517
00:29:09,628 --> 00:29:12,196
<i>Chandler: We can't fire
with them right below us.</i>

518
00:29:12,197 --> 00:29:14,465
Come to full power! All
engines ahead, flank three!

519
00:29:14,466 --> 00:29:16,460
<i>Gator: All engines ahead, flank three, aye!</i>

520
00:29:16,465 --> 00:29:18,453
[Engines roar]

521
00:29:20,362 --> 00:29:21,776
We need room.

522
00:29:21,787 --> 00:29:23,769
Engines, all ahead full.

523
00:29:23,774 --> 00:29:25,018
Aye, sir!

524
00:29:26,053 --> 00:29:27,392
They're accelerating.

525
00:29:27,404 --> 00:29:28,479
Right 20-degree rudder.

526
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:29,847
Stay on him!

527
00:29:29,848 --> 00:29:32,850
C.I.C., prepare to fire. Yes, sir.

528
00:29:34,018 --> 00:29:35,207
Is he turning?

529
00:29:35,220 --> 00:29:36,387
Stay under him.

530
00:29:36,388 --> 00:29:39,127
As soon as the bottom drops off,
we dive and fire on my order.

531
00:29:39,128 --> 00:29:40,137
Aye!

532
00:29:40,152 --> 00:29:41,391
Stay on them!

533
00:29:41,392 --> 00:29:42,443
How fast are they moving?

534
00:29:42,458 --> 00:29:43,952
Approaching 30 knots, sir.

535
00:29:43,962 --> 00:29:45,813
He's going too fast.

536
00:29:45,953 --> 00:29:49,255
CCS, disengage rev limiters.
Override engine safeties.

537
00:29:49,389 --> 00:29:51,274
Come on. Kick it into overdrive.

538
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:52,964
I got a surprise for you.

539
00:29:54,119 --> 00:29:56,544
<i>O'Connor: Come on! We need more ice!</i>

540
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:59,798
Come on, baby! Stay with me!

541
00:29:59,801 --> 00:30:01,147
Fire torpedoes, sir?

542
00:30:01,159 --> 00:30:03,714
Too close. They're almost right above us.

543
00:30:03,715 --> 00:30:05,080
I'm ready to fire right now, sir.

544
00:30:05,091 --> 00:30:06,776
We'll blow ourselves bloody up!

545
00:30:06,784 --> 00:30:08,995
We can stay under him
until we reach deep water.

546
00:30:08,998 --> 00:30:11,340
We're coming up on deep
water! He's gonna dive!

547
00:30:11,342 --> 00:30:12,789
How long before we can dive?

548
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:14,416
Two klicks to the trench, sir.

549
00:30:14,425 --> 00:30:16,126
They have to know we're
running for the deep.

550
00:30:16,127 --> 00:30:17,859
They're gonna make a move any second.

551
00:30:19,563 --> 00:30:22,750
On my mark, all back full!

552
00:30:22,751 --> 00:30:23,917
Arm torpedoes.

553
00:30:23,930 --> 00:30:24,958
Aye, sir!

554
00:30:24,959 --> 00:30:26,855
Call it out when we can dive. Yes, sir!

555
00:30:26,861 --> 00:30:27,971
Engage emergency power.

556
00:30:28,063 --> 00:30:29,544
Engaging!

557
00:30:34,101 --> 00:30:35,635
500 meters from the shelf!

558
00:30:35,636 --> 00:30:36,970
- Prepare to fire.
- Aye, sir.

559
00:30:36,971 --> 00:30:39,072
Fire while diving. Release at 100 meters.

560
00:30:39,073 --> 00:30:40,707
Prepare to dive!

561
00:30:40,708 --> 00:30:41,753
Come on! More ice!

562
00:30:41,768 --> 00:30:43,249
[Electricity crackling]

563
00:30:43,259 --> 00:30:45,239
This thing's going!

564
00:30:47,106 --> 00:30:48,554
No sonar!

565
00:30:48,565 --> 00:30:51,156
Dive now! Dive! Dive! Dive!

566
00:30:51,157 --> 00:30:53,954
[Klaxon blaring]

567
00:30:53,955 --> 00:30:55,011
We're at the drop-off, sir!

568
00:30:55,026 --> 00:30:57,243
All engines back full!

569
00:30:57,246 --> 00:30:58,862
[Engines roar]

570
00:30:58,871 --> 00:31:00,656
Unh!

571
00:31:03,642 --> 00:31:05,259
Fire torpedoes!

572
00:31:05,268 --> 00:31:08,167
Four downrange now!

573
00:31:14,324 --> 00:31:15,941
[Gasps]

574
00:31:15,950 --> 00:31:17,703
Man your station.

575
00:31:20,398 --> 00:31:22,622
85 meters!

576
00:31:22,625 --> 00:31:24,250
90! 95!

577
00:31:24,259 --> 00:31:25,470
Call it!

578
00:31:25,483 --> 00:31:27,457
Fire torpedoes!

579
00:31:30,570 --> 00:31:32,894
Hydrophone effects! We've got incoming!

580
00:31:32,896 --> 00:31:34,343
I count three!

581
00:31:34,354 --> 00:31:35,431
Now four!

582
00:31:35,445 --> 00:31:36,386
Emergency dive!

583
00:31:36,397 --> 00:31:39,024
Full ahead! Point her down!

584
00:31:42,301 --> 00:31:45,093
T.A.O., what's the status of our torpedoes?

585
00:31:45,094 --> 00:31:47,147
Captain, we're blind here. Sonar's out.

586
00:31:47,152 --> 00:31:48,836
He's probably launched on us.

587
00:31:48,844 --> 00:31:50,337
Hard right rudder!

588
00:31:50,347 --> 00:31:53,167
[Engines roar]

589
00:31:53,938 --> 00:31:56,262
Activate prairie/masker air.

590
00:31:56,264 --> 00:31:58,258
Launch acoustic decoys.

591
00:32:00,473 --> 00:32:02,459
[Rapid beeping]

592
00:32:02,975 --> 00:32:05,618
- [Beeping quickens]
- Shit!

593
00:32:12,993 --> 00:32:16,362
I need eyes out there.
Did we hit them or not?

594
00:32:17,580 --> 00:32:20,329
<i>Man: Torpedo trails, portside, 0-1-0!</i>

595
00:32:20,330 --> 00:32:21,498
All hands, brace for shock!

596
00:32:21,511 --> 00:32:22,891
Holy shit!

597
00:32:24,464 --> 00:32:25,980
- [Alarm blaring]
- We're hit!

598
00:32:25,990 --> 00:32:29,282
D.C. central, dispatch
teams to portside midships.

599
00:32:29,283 --> 00:32:32,287
Fire on deck 4, portside amidships!

600
00:32:32,288 --> 00:32:35,046
Fire in the magazine! Fire in the magazine!

601
00:32:35,047 --> 00:32:36,615
<i>Man: Captain, fire in the weapons room!</i>

602
00:32:36,624 --> 00:32:38,890
Flood it! Flood projectiles magazine!

603
00:32:38,893 --> 00:32:41,355
Port shaft is down! No
turns on portside shaft!

604
00:32:41,356 --> 00:32:44,381
Enable shaft seal. Head 2-9-0.
Maintain evasive action.

605
00:32:44,382 --> 00:32:45,340
Seal compartments,

606
00:32:45,356 --> 00:32:47,934
frames 7-2 through 1-2-4,
decks 4, 5, and 6.

607
00:32:47,935 --> 00:32:49,117
Set primary boundaries...

608
00:32:49,130 --> 00:32:51,523
Frames 7-2 through 1-2-4,
decks 4, 5, and 6.

609
00:32:51,524 --> 00:32:53,982
[Blaring continues]

610
00:33:02,362 --> 00:33:05,418
Commander! O'Connor!

611
00:33:05,419 --> 00:33:06,435
Come on!

612
00:33:06,450 --> 00:33:08,706
Ship's flooding! They're
gonna seal us in here!

613
00:33:08,709 --> 00:33:10,484
Ma'am, come on!

614
00:33:10,491 --> 00:33:12,790
[Gasping]

615
00:33:12,794 --> 00:33:15,722
Come on. This way.

616
00:33:23,143 --> 00:33:24,673
T.A.O. Status.

617
00:33:24,683 --> 00:33:26,306
Did we hit that sub or not?

618
00:33:26,307 --> 00:33:27,874
We cannot confirm, sir.

619
00:33:27,875 --> 00:33:29,342
<i>Alisha: Magazine's flooded, sir.</i>

620
00:33:29,343 --> 00:33:31,296
We're out of weapons.

621
00:33:31,302 --> 00:33:34,071
♪

622
00:33:40,540 --> 00:33:43,223
<i>Woman: Yeah. She's getting better.</i>

623
00:33:45,679 --> 00:33:47,747
What are you doing, Doc?

624
00:33:47,748 --> 00:33:50,966
Documenting history.

625
00:33:51,253 --> 00:33:53,677
A contagious cure.

626
00:34:00,918 --> 00:34:03,984
[Static]

627
00:34:06,509 --> 00:34:08,710
Any word?

628
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:10,228
Nothing.

629
00:34:11,447 --> 00:34:13,468
T.A.O., what's left in the holster?

630
00:34:13,473 --> 00:34:14,931
Just the rounds in the 5-inch, sir.

631
00:34:14,942 --> 00:34:16,187
How many?

632
00:34:17,500 --> 00:34:19,449
Four.

633
00:34:22,615 --> 00:34:25,217
If all we got are surface weapons,

634
00:34:25,218 --> 00:34:28,053
we'll make this a surface fight.

635
00:34:28,054 --> 00:34:30,489
Head 2-9-5. Go for shallow water.

636
00:34:30,490 --> 00:34:33,559
We'll make that sub show its ugly face.

637
00:34:36,562 --> 00:34:37,864
[Alarm blaring]

638
00:34:37,865 --> 00:34:40,299
<i>Oliver: Switching to emergency generators!</i>

639
00:34:40,300 --> 00:34:42,902
Pressure hull's buckled,
sir! We got to surface!

640
00:34:42,903 --> 00:34:44,337
Shut your mouth!

641
00:34:44,338 --> 00:34:45,972
Turn for target!

642
00:34:45,973 --> 00:34:48,941
Back at them?! Are you completely mad?!

643
00:34:48,942 --> 00:34:51,411
He said, "turn to target," mate! Do it!

644
00:34:51,412 --> 00:34:53,780
Drive them to the rocket battery!

645
00:34:53,781 --> 00:34:56,339
Get us to periscope depth!

646
00:35:03,856 --> 00:35:06,451
Guys, have a look.

647
00:35:08,094 --> 00:35:10,329
That's a truck hauling something heavy.

648
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:12,350
Yeah.

649
00:35:12,417 --> 00:35:14,216
On me.

650
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:29,182
Ooh. That is some piece of hardware.

651
00:35:29,183 --> 00:35:31,249
That's a ship killer, all right.

652
00:35:31,254 --> 00:35:34,087
One of those warheads hits
the <i>James,</i> she's sunk.

653
00:35:34,088 --> 00:35:36,689
<i>Danny: Looks like the same
guys we fought on</i> Solace.

654
00:35:36,690 --> 00:35:38,171
I count seven.

655
00:35:38,181 --> 00:35:40,917
Well, let's see if we
can take that bad boy out.

656
00:35:41,283 --> 00:35:42,916
X.O.

657
00:35:49,200 --> 00:35:51,826
Oh, Tommy. What'd you go and do?

658
00:35:51,827 --> 00:35:54,505
Sir, approaching shoal water fast.

659
00:35:54,506 --> 00:35:55,441
How deep?

660
00:35:55,442 --> 00:35:58,606
35 feet below the keel.
Seabed's rock here, sir.

661
00:35:58,607 --> 00:36:00,513
If we touch at this speed, we're
gonna take the bottom out of the ship.

662
00:36:00,514 --> 00:36:02,641
Not much longer.

663
00:36:02,645 --> 00:36:05,777
<i>Slattery: It's too late to warn the
ship. They're already in firing range.</i>

664
00:36:06,185 --> 00:36:08,855
Okay. Here's the plan, boys.

665
00:36:08,856 --> 00:36:10,523
Win.

666
00:36:10,524 --> 00:36:11,791
Good plan.

667
00:36:11,792 --> 00:36:14,216
♪

668
00:36:18,064 --> 00:36:22,068
Not long, guys. This is
what we've been waiting for.

669
00:36:22,069 --> 00:36:24,170
I'll draw their fire.

670
00:36:26,131 --> 00:36:28,371
[Machine-gun fire]

671
00:37:06,412 --> 00:37:08,365
Cover me!

672
00:37:24,330 --> 00:37:26,565
[Whirring]

673
00:37:32,878 --> 00:37:35,340
<i>Oliver: Dead to rights at 2-9-0!</i>

674
00:37:35,341 --> 00:37:36,508
All full ahead.

675
00:37:36,509 --> 00:37:37,509
Aye, sir.

676
00:37:37,510 --> 00:37:39,052
- Arm torpedoes.
- Aye, sir.

677
00:37:39,062 --> 00:37:42,781
Submarine on our 6:00,
200 meters, bearing 2-9-5.

678
00:37:42,782 --> 00:37:44,263
They're accelerating!

679
00:37:44,273 --> 00:37:47,041
[Gun cocks]

680
00:37:51,446 --> 00:37:54,205
<i>Max: 400 meters, sir! Locked on target!</i>

681
00:37:54,206 --> 00:37:56,234
Prepare to fire!

682
00:37:56,576 --> 00:37:59,302
<i>Gator: Submarine 300 meters,
coming straight at us, sir!</i>

683
00:37:59,303 --> 00:38:02,243
Buttonhook starboard!

684
00:38:05,748 --> 00:38:08,774
Aren't you a little old for this? Eh?

685
00:38:08,775 --> 00:38:09,855
Aaaah!

686
00:38:09,869 --> 00:38:12,678
- Come on!
- [Grunts]

687
00:38:14,920 --> 00:38:16,166
[Bones crack]

688
00:38:16,179 --> 00:38:19,142
[Both groaning, grunting]

689
00:38:19,707 --> 00:38:21,287
Aaaaah!

690
00:38:21,296 --> 00:38:23,971
- [Knife plunges]
- Unggggggh!

691
00:38:29,546 --> 00:38:33,172
T.A.O., fire control will
fire as 5-inch bears on target

692
00:38:33,173 --> 00:38:34,471
- on your call.
- Aye, sir.

693
00:38:34,483 --> 00:38:37,253
Once that sub clears our
superstructure, we fire.

694
00:38:37,254 --> 00:38:38,744
[Whirring]

695
00:38:38,754 --> 00:38:42,040
Solved! On your order, sir!

696
00:38:42,041 --> 00:38:44,243
Sub's locked on us! They're going to fire!

697
00:38:44,244 --> 00:38:45,900
<i>Kara: Sir, we still don't have a shot.</i>

698
00:38:45,909 --> 00:38:48,421
Maintain heading!

699
00:38:48,421 --> 00:38:49,911
And...

700
00:38:59,424 --> 00:39:01,479
- [Chuckling]
- Cheers, asshole.

701
00:39:01,484 --> 00:39:03,558
T.A.O., let's finish the job.

702
00:39:03,562 --> 00:39:04,975
Fire four at will.

703
00:39:04,986 --> 00:39:06,501
Abandon ship!

704
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:08,968
- [Indistinct shouting]
- Get back! Get back to your posts!

705
00:39:09,068 --> 00:39:12,304
Get back to your posts! That's an order!

706
00:39:12,305 --> 00:39:13,895
We're chosen!

707
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:30,416
[Sighs]

708
00:39:31,045 --> 00:39:33,065
[Explosions in distance]

709
00:39:33,543 --> 00:39:35,867
[Explosions continue]

710
00:39:45,546 --> 00:39:47,736
<i>Gator: We did it, sir.</i>

711
00:39:47,739 --> 00:39:50,351
We did it.

712
00:40:01,353 --> 00:40:03,610
[Panting]

713
00:40:06,556 --> 00:40:09,607
<i>Tex: That is a damn fine sight.</i>

714
00:40:09,753 --> 00:40:12,346
Amen.

715
00:40:12,799 --> 00:40:14,766
Vulture Team...

716
00:40:14,767 --> 00:40:16,668
The sub is sinking.

717
00:40:16,669 --> 00:40:17,736
Saddle up.

718
00:40:17,737 --> 00:40:19,555
We're headed home.

719
00:40:20,539 --> 00:40:21,886
It's over.

720
00:40:23,113 --> 00:40:24,932
It's over.

721
00:40:24,939 --> 00:40:26,656
Come here.

722
00:40:31,548 --> 00:40:33,637
Thank you.

723
00:40:36,444 --> 00:40:38,499
<i>Michener: It worked.</i>

724
00:40:38,629 --> 00:40:42,469
Your cure... It's a miracle.

725
00:40:53,125 --> 00:40:55,382
♪

726
00:41:06,238 --> 00:41:09,625
[Electricity crackling, metal creaking]

727
00:41:21,694 --> 00:41:25,336
[Screams]

728
